@node Tutorial 1 Electrostatic field around a microstrip line
@section Tutorial 1: Electrostatic field around a microstrip line
A 2D electrostatic model of a microstrip line is considered, with only one half of the geometry modelled by symmetry. A 1mV voltage is imposed on the microstrip line, which sits on top of a dielectric substrate grounded on its lower side.

@center@image{images/01-Electrostatics,14cm,,Screenshot of tutorial 01-Electrostatics}
@center See @url{https://gitlab.onelab.info/getdp/tutorials/-/tree/main/01-Electrostatics,tutorials/01-Electrostatics}.


@subsection Features
@itemize
@item
Electrostatic model in terms of the electric scalar potential
@item
Physical and abstract regions
@item
Scalar function space with Lagrange elements and Dirichlet constraint
@end itemize

See the comments in @code{microstrip.pro} and @code{microstrip.geo} for details.

@subsection Running the tutorial
Each tutorial consists of (at least) two input files: a ``.geo'' file describing the geometry and the meshing constraints (the Gmsh part of the setup), and a ``.pro'' file describing the differential equations to solve together with the associated function spaces, boundary conditions and solver parameters (the GetDP part of the setup).

To run the tutorial on the command line:

@verbatim
> gmsh microstrip.geo -2
> getdp microstrip.pro -solve Ele -pos Map
@end verbatim

To run the tutorial interactively with Gmsh: open @code{microstrip.pro} with ``File->Open'', then press ``Run''.
