@node Tutorial 3 Magnetostatic model of an electromagnet
@section Tutorial 3: Magnetostatic model of an electromagnet
A 2D magnetostatic model of an electromagnet is considered. A current density is imposed in the coil, and the ferromagnetic core can be modelled either using a linear or a nonlinear constitutive law. Infinite elements are used to accurately model the unbounded domain.

@center@image{images/03-Magnetostatics,14cm,,Screenshot of tutorial 03-Magnetostatics}
@center See @url{https://gitlab.onelab.info/getdp/tutorials/-/tree/main/03-Magnetostatics,tutorials/03-Magnetostatics}.


@subsection Features
@itemize
@item
Magnetostatic model in terms of the magnetic vector potential
@item
Infinite ring geometrical transformation
@item
Function space for the 2D vector potential (``perpendicular edges'')
@item
Newton-Raphson and Picard linearization schemes
@end itemize

See the comments in @code{electromagnet.pro} and @code{electromagnet.geo} for details.

@subsection Running the tutorial
On the command line:

@verbatim
> gmsh electromagnet.geo -2
> getdp electromagnet.pro -solve Mag -pos Map
@end verbatim

Interactively with Gmsh: open @code{electromagnet.pro} with ``File->Open'', then press ``Run''.
